              <chunks count="1">
                <chunk name="Container">
                  <items count="8">
                    <item name="Description" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">A panel for custom notes and text values</item>
                    <item name="InstanceGuid" type_name="gh_guid" type_code="9">5cdb0475-eeda-4be6-8343-60bc85897dfe</item>
                    <item name="Name" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">Panel</item>
                    <item name="NickName" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">HOLOPHONIX EXPORT — v1.0.0
</item>
                    <item name="Optional" type_name="gh_bool" type_code="1">false</item>
                    <item name="ScrollRatio" type_name="gh_double" type_code="6">0</item>
                    <item name="SourceCount" type_name="gh_int32" type_code="3">0</item>
                    <item name="UserText" type_name="gh_string" type_code="10">github.com/aker-dev/holophonix_export
Export a Rhino 8 scene to a Holophonix
package. Requires Rhino &gt;= 8.3.

── INPUTS ──────────────────────────────
folder           output folder (CSV + .glb)
run              ▶ write CSV + GLBs
layer_root       speakers prefix (SPEAKERS)
auto_orient      true/false column
export_venue     write venue.glb
export_speakers  one .glb per model
sync             ▶ push to Holophonix via OSC
osc_host         default 127.0.0.1
osc_port         default 4003

── OUTPUTS ─────────────────────────────
lines   CSV preview (header + rows)
count   number of speakers
log     diagnostics

── RHINO SCENE ─────────────────────────
Speakers : Block Instances on sub-layers
           of SPEAKERS:: (ex SPEAKERS::MDC5).
           Layer color = speaker color.
           Block Name attribute optional,
           inserted as LAYER_NAME_NN.
Venue    : any geometry on VENUE or VENUE::*.

── WORKFLOW ────────────────────────────
1. Set `folder`, click `run` once:
     holophonix_overview.csv
     venue.glb               (if toggled)
     &lt;MODEL&gt;.glb per model   (if toggled)
2. In Holophonix:
     - import CSV via Overview window
     - load .glb as 3D assets
3. After moving speakers in Rhino,
   click `sync` → live update over OSC.

── NOTES ───────────────────────────────
Block forward axis  = local -Y
Axis mapping (R→H)  = (Y_r, X_r, Z_r)
OSC only UPDATES existing speakers —
the CSV import must have created them first.</item>
